Hello, my name is Shane, and welcome to Turo!

I am a small business owner who is doing Turo to supplement the income earned in my small business to keep the lights on and my employees working.   In these difficult times it's hard to stay afloat in a small business.  So my team and I work hard to do this with the same level of commitment that we do in all the services we provide.

I have a growing Turo fleet with a focus on providing affordable, reliable, and economical cars for anyone who needs a vehicle.

We have a solid process for contactless pickup - meaning I won't actually be there when you pick up the vehicle. This gives you a more convenient and flexible booking and rental experience. 

Though all of my cars have wear and tear they are all meticulously maintained, they are all cleaned and disinfected between every single rental and they will all get you to where you need to go at an affordable price. 

My Turo profile speaks for itself, if you are looking for a host you can count on than look no further than my fleet of vehicles.

Hello there and welcome! Thank you for taking the time out to scroll through my profile!

My name is Iziah and I am pleased to share the same wonderful experiences with my vehicles to you. I have a distinct background in helping and fulfilling other's needs.

I am getting married soon in 2022 and I really needed help with being able to give my Fiancé the wedding she always dreamed of. I needed more income, but it had to be "passive" income as I have a full-time job and have a one year old at home with me. 

In the beginning of the year of 2021, I tried to get my Grandmother a rental car to go out of town. Every rental car company was sold out within a 100 mile radius and I did not understand why or how. I did a little research and seen that most rental car companies took a big hit during the pandemic and had to file for bankruptcy or sell their fleet...DING (Lightbulb inside my head turned on). I did more research to see how the world was handling the situation and what were the alternatives.

On YouTube, I came across somebody in Atlanta who had videos on his experiences and earnings on Turo and how this was the Airbnb on wheels. I thought this was the perfect idea for passive income to help pay for my wedding. To make sure I was making a wise decision, I used my personal car to see how it goes.

Fast forward, I now have a small fleet of 8 cars and business is booming. Not only, am I able to make extra payments for the wedding, but also able to endure and invest in more projects. What has made me successful, is to provide excellent customer service being a service provider.

Thank you for taking the time out to read my Bio and learning a little bit more about me and my services. I hope to meet you soon, safe travels!

Customer service is important to me. Respecting vehicles shows a lot about your character. When I rent cars on turo or other platforms, I make it my duty to bring the cars back the same way I got it. I respect peoples property. Please do the same. Who wants to trash out these beautiful cars?
